3":"1225–1273","1225":"1225","January 1298":"January 1298","1386":"1386","1265":"1265","1298":"1298","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England":"Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Loring","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: ethnic name from Old French <i>Lohereng</i> ‘man fromLorraine’ (see   Lorraine  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Lorne","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from the district of Lorn (Argyll).","English: perhaps a shortened form of   Loring  , a surname which is well evidenced in medieval southwestern England, where <i>Lorne</i> is later recorded."]},{"name":"Lorraine","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Emile, Perrine, Pierre.","French and English: habitational name from Lorraine, a region in the northeastern part of France. Its name derives from the name of the medieval kingdom of Lotharingia, which in turn was named for its sovereign <i>Lothar</i> (a personal name composed of the elements <i>hlūd</i> ‘famous, renowned’ + <i>hari</i>, <i>heri</i> ‘army’).","Altered form of French   Lorrain  , a variant of 1 above."]}]},{"name":"Peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":30,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Peter Loring was born in 1260, in Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England as the son of Peter de Loring. He had at least 1 son with Jane Morteyn. He died in January 1298, in Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 38."},"et":{"1260–January 1298":"1260–jaanuar 1298","1260–1298":"1260–1298","1265–1290":"1265–1290","1290–1386":"1290–1386","1225–1273":"1225–1273","1225":"1225","January 1298":"jaanuar 1298","1386":"1386","1265":"1265","1298":"1298","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England":"Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1260–January 1298":"1260–tammikuu 1298","1260–1298":"1260–1298","1265–1290":"1265–1290","1290–1386":"1290–1386","1225–1273":"1225–1273","1225":"1225","January 1298":"tammikuu 1298","1386":"1386","1265":"1265","1298":"1298","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England":"Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1260–January 1298":"1260–janvier 1298","1260–1298":"1260–1298","1265–1290":"1265–1290","1290–1386":"1290–1386","1225–1273":"1225–1273","1225":"1225","January 1298":"janvier 1298","1386":"1386","1265":"1265","1298":"1298","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England":"Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Peter Loring est né e